         <listPlace>
            <place type="church monastery" subtype="institution">
               <placeName>ʾAgärhǝse ʾAbunä Mamas</placeName>
               <placeName type="alt">Däbrä Qǝddusan ʾAbunä Mamas ʾAgärhǝse</placeName>
               <country>Ethiopia</country>
               <region>Tǝgray</region>
               <settlement from="2010-11-16" to="2010-11-16">wäräda Gulo Mäkäda, ṭabiya Šäwit Lämläm, qušät ʾAgärhǝse</settlement>
               <location>
                  <geo>14.44875 39.342167</geo>
                  <height unit="m">2312.0</height>
               </location>
               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1300" notAfter="1400">1300-1400</date>
                  <desc type="foundation">The date provided by the local tradition is 1295 year of mercy. Accodring to local tradition, the
                     founder was ʾabunä Mamas (from the time of King ʿAmdä Ṣǝyon I, r.
                     1314-44).</desc>
                  <ab type="history">Gätär. According to the Vita of saint Bä-ṣälotä Mikaʾel of Däbrä Gol (ʾAmhara), he was exiled to Gulo Mäkäda and died at Gwǝdgwǝde, which seems to have been a name of the area around ʾAgärhǝse. Local tradition remembers him and confirms that his burial place is in the vicinity. &#xD;
</ab>
                  <ab type="description">25 Mss.; 10 Mss. photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm001">AQM-001</ref> "Vita of Mamas"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm002">AQM-002</ref> "Vita of Mamas"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm003">AQM-003</ref> "Four Gospels"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm004">AQM-004</ref> "The Book of the Baptismal Rite"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm005">AQM-005</ref> "Miracles of Jesus"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm006">AQM-006</ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm007">AQM-007</ref> "Miracles of Jesus"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm008">AQM-008</ref> "Missal"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm009">AQM-009</ref> "Missal"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm010">AQM-010</ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"</ab>
  
